commitResults.messageBody:
# Changes
- There was a bug where the `edit` command was not being recommended for
auto complete, as it was always choosing the `edit_elderly` command
first. I modified the `findMatchingCommandInfo` method slightly:
- The method now accepts an additional argument `isExactMatching`. If
true, it will return the command with the exact matching to
`commandWord` (This is used when we know it's a "complete" command).
Otherwise, it will just perform a prefix matching as per normal.
- After filtering, we first sort the commands: This is so that shorter
and lexicographically smaller commands will get recommended first
- Modified the NRIC prefixes for the add commands to just use `nr\`
instead
- Modified the constraint message for `BirthDate` to better match the
regex given.

Currently, FriendlyLink checks for differing region of elderly and volunteers to indicate a warning should be thrown.

This implementation prevents other types of warning to be indicated since FriendlyLink can only return true or false instead of indicating the warning.

Let's refactor region check to take place in AddPairCommand instead of FriendlyLink so that it can raise different warnings.

# Changes
- Add the `auto_pair` command with relevant tests

volunteers and elderly. Performing a maximum matching is possible, but I
was concerned about potential bugs, so I avoided it.
- Add command to the UG (I also edited the example command for adding
elderly as well, because might as well)

for better abstraction
